<HEADLINE>
FT  27 AUG 94 / UK Company News: New London reduces losses to Dollars 3.25m
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
New London, the oil industry services company, reported sharply reduced
pre-tax losses of Dollars 3.25m (Pounds 2m) for the year to March 31,
against Dollars 23.7m.
The result was achieved on turnover halved at Dollars 71.9m (Dollars
135.9m), which included Dollars 46.6m from discontinued activities.
Pre-interest losses were Dollars 2.96m (Dollars 20.2m) including Dollars
1.6m from discontinued activities.
Net interest charges fell from Dollars 3.55m to Dollars 293,000. Losses per
share were 3.3 cents (23.2 cents).
Mr Paul Kesterton, chairman, said the year was affected by the disposal of
International Drilling Fluids to Schlumberger which was completed on
September 1. The result included a five months' contribution from IDF and
was struck after a loss on disposals of Dollars 12.2m offset by a prior year
provision of Dollars 12.3m.
The total consideration for IDF was Dollars 11.4m plus the acceptance of
Dollars 30m of bank debt. During the period New London also paid Dollars 10m
and 12m shares to Electra Private Equity Partners to repay debt and deferred
interest.
</TEXT>
