temporary', saying the force was specially trained and equipped. At least 17
people have died from cholera, a further 686 are ill and 669 have been
diagnosed as carrying the disease, which can kill in a few hours by severe
dehydration from diarrhoea. A senior Moscow health official said on
Wednesday that it would take until mid-October to eliminate the epidemic.
