<HEADLINE>
FT  26 AUG 94 / International Company News: Singapore Press Holdings raises
USDollars 200m
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By ANTONIA SHARPE
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
Singapore Press Holdings, the island republic's largest publishing group,
has raised close to USDollars 200m through the private placement of foreign
shares with institutional investors.
The 11m new shares, which account for about 4 per cent of the company's
share capital, were priced at SDollars 26 each. This represents a 1.9 per
cent discount to the last traded price on the foreign shares on August 22.
Lead manager BZW said the new equity would raise the percentage of foreign
ownership of the company to close to the maximum level of 49 per cent.
There is a restriction on foreign ownership because the company controls the
media in Singapore.
