<HEADLINE>
FT  26 AUG 94 / UK Company News: Pounds 4.78m non-core sales by UK Safety
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
UK Safety, the footwear manufacturer, has raised a further Pounds 4.78m from
the sale of non-core assets acquired when it reversed into TSW-Television
South West, the former independent television con-tractor.
It has sold its remaining holding in Societe Europeennes des Satellites, the
operator of the Astra satellites, for Pounds 4.08m, a surplus over book
value of Pounds 2.3m, making a total profit on the whole disposal of Pounds
3m.
It is also selling the studios and former offices of TSW in Plymouth for
Pounds 700,000, producing a loss of Pounds 550,000 against book value.
