FT  26 AUG 94 / Israeli rabbis tour Hebron's Tomb of the Patriarchs
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
Israel's two chief rabbis, Ashkenazi Rabbi Yisrael Lau (right) and Sephardic
Rabbi Eliahu Bakshi-Doron (left) surrounded by Israeli army and border
police officers as they tour the grounds of the Tomb of the Patriarchs in
Hebron yesterday, six months to the day after the massacre of 30
Palestinians by an American-born Jewish settler, Baruch Goldstein. The
incident touched off months of bloodshed and disrupted the Middle East peace
process. The tomb, holy to both Jews and Moslems, has been closed since the
massacre. Both are demanding the site be re-opened. Hebron is one of the
most tense spots in the Israeli-controlled West Bank, as home to about
80,000 Palestinians as well as a Jewish enclave of 450.
