<HEADLINE>
FT  26 AUG 94 / Economic Watch: Gains in French housing starts continue
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
French housing starts continued to show gains in the three months to July.
Figures from the housing ministry showed work began on 73,200 homes in the
three months from May to July compared with 71,700 in April-June. May-July
housing starts were 23.0 per cent up on the same 1993 period.
