<HEADLINE>
FT  25 AUG 94 / World Trade News: US sees air travel up 5% in 1993
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By AP
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
   WASHINGTON
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
The US Transportation Department says 1993 was the busiest year ever for air
travel between the US and other countries, with 92.5m passengers, up 5 per
cent from 1992, AP reports from Washington.
US airlines carried 54 per cent of that traffic, an increase of 1 percentage
point from 1992, the department said.
It was also a record year for international air freight, totaling nearly
4.7m tons, a 10 per cent increase over the previous year. US airlines
carried 41 per cent of the freight traffic, also a one-point increase over
1992.
