<HEADLINE>
FT  25 AUG 94 / International Company News: NRMA sees ADollars 215m profits
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By NIKKI TAIT
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
   SYDNEY
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
NRMA, Australia's largest motorists' organisation and one of its biggest
general insurers, yesterday forecast that it would make after-tax profits of
ADollars 215m (USDollars 158m) in the year to end-June 1995.
This would represent a sharp turnround from the ADollars 129m scored in the
year just ended, although realised losses of ADollars 128m in 1993-94 were
abnormally high and depressed the result. In 1992-93 and 1991-92, NRMA's net
profits were ADollars 248m and ADollars 261m respectively.
</TEXT>
<XX>
Companies:-
</XX>
