<HEADLINE>
FT  25 AUG 94 / UK Company News: Gibbs &amp; Dandy up to Pounds 425,000
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
Against a background of fierce competition, sales at Gibbs &amp; Dandy, the
builders' merchant, rose by 5 per cent to Pounds 11.9m and pre-tax profits
climbed from Pounds 292,000 to Pounds 425,000.
Mr John Dandy, chairman, said the sales trend had continued and reflected
the tentative recovery in the construction industry.
Earnings per share advanced from 2.5p to 4.6p.
The interim dividend is raised to 1.2p (1p) and a final of at least 1.8p
(1.5p) is forecast.
</TEXT>
